shellesc package

Shell escape macros

\ShellEscape{some commands}
  Execute some commands in the shell if that is allowed

\DelayedShellEscape{some commands}
  Execute some commands in the shell if that is allowed
  the command will be executed as teh current page is being shipped out

\immediate\write18{some commands}
  An alias for \ShellEscape
  (On platforms other than luatex this is the primitive syntax for shell escape)



To produce typeset documentation:
pdflatex shellesc.dtx

To extract the shellesc.sty package:
tex shellesc.ins

